criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients attending the outpatient service of Hospital das Clínicas, São Paulo, Brazil.

          -  ≥ 30 years.

          -  at least two measurements of creatinine (with a minimum interval of 3 months) ≥ 1.6
             mg/dl for men and ≥ 1.4 mg/ dl for women.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients attending oncology, psychiatry, human immunodeficiency virus/acquired
             immunodeficiency syndrome (HIV/AIDS), viral hepatitis and glomerulonephritis services
             were excluded.

          -  hospitalization within the last six months;

          -  acute myocardial infarction within the last six months;

          -  autoimmune diseases;

          -  current pregnancy;

          -  psychiatric diseases;

          -  ongoing chemotherapy or immunosuppressive therapy;

          -  current renal replacement therapy;

          -  HIV/AIDS infection;

          -  hepatitis B or C;

          -  any organ transplantation.
